1
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:21,633
As far as I remember...

2
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:23,933
after you carved that,

3
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:25,633
you wanted to kiss me.

4
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:26,600
But I didn't want to.

5
00:00:26,667 --> 00:00:28,133
I didn't allow you.

6
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:29,667
You're terrible.
We just became ex-lovers

7
00:00:29,733 --> 00:00:31,767
and you edit the truth.

8
00:00:31,833 --> 00:00:33,833
I said I love you so much.

9
00:00:33,900 --> 00:00:35,033
Will you not answer me?

10
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:38,233
I love you so much, Celeste!

11
00:00:38,300 --> 00:00:39,467
I love you!

12
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:43,233
What? Do you remember now?

13
00:00:43,300 --> 00:00:46,100
By the way, this is Mikoy,
my childhood friend.

14
00:00:46,167 --> 00:00:49,133
He actually took care of me
when I got stranded.

15
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:50,633
I owe my life to him.

16
00:00:50,700 --> 00:00:51,600
If weren't for him

17
00:00:51,667 --> 00:00:53,833
maybe something bad happened
to me.

18
00:00:53,900 --> 00:00:57,100
What are your plans
for the wedding?

19
00:00:57,167 --> 00:00:58,600
All I want to do is make Celeste

20
00:00:58,667 --> 00:01:00,833
the happiest woman in the world.

21
00:01:00,900 --> 00:01:03,033
I never dreamed of finding
the right woman.

22
00:01:03,100 --> 00:01:04,700
And now I just want
to be the right man

23
00:01:04,767 --> 00:01:06,233
for the woman I will love.

24
00:01:06,300 --> 00:01:11,067
Oh my God. Why is it like this?

25
00:01:11,167 --> 00:01:12,500
Why am I thinking of Mikoy?

26
00:01:12,567 --> 00:01:16,067
Can I erase, erase, erase?

27
00:01:16,133 --> 00:01:18,767
I think that fool casts
a spell on me.

28
00:01:25,333 --> 00:01:27,733
Oh, Mother.

29
00:01:27,800 --> 00:01:29,133
What's this?

30
00:01:30,367 --> 00:01:30,933
Mother, why is it like this?

31
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,067
I'm so confused.

32
00:01:32,133 --> 00:01:37,100
Why is it like this?
Why am I thinking of Mikoy?

33
00:01:37,167 --> 00:01:39,467
He's coming in my mind.

34
00:01:39,533 --> 00:01:40,833
Why is that?

35
00:01:42,700 --> 00:01:43,867
I'm so confused.

36
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:48,633
Wait a second.

37
00:01:48,700 --> 00:01:50,600
Come here. Wait a second.

38
00:01:50,667 --> 00:01:54,133
There.

39
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,733
Hold it for a second.

40
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:04,167
Where did you learn that?

41
00:02:04,233 --> 00:02:05,467
I'm a boy scout.

42
00:02:05,533 --> 00:02:07,633
I'm always prepared.

43
00:02:07,700 --> 00:02:09,000
Just wait.

44
00:02:11,633 --> 00:02:12,800
- Here?
- Yes.

45
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:18,000
My foot is dirty.

46
00:02:18,067 --> 00:02:19,567
That's okay.

47
00:02:21,433 --> 00:02:22,433
It's okay now.

48
00:02:30,933 --> 00:02:33,433
Come here.

49
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:35,233
You're cold, right?

50
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:50,633
Just go to sleep.

51
00:02:50,700 --> 00:02:52,133
I'll watch over you.

52
00:03:10,067 --> 00:03:11,300
Close your eyes.

53
00:03:27,433 --> 00:03:30,300
Ready, ouch!

54
00:03:30,367 --> 00:03:31,200
You're heavy!

55
00:03:33,067 --> 00:03:34,500
Let's go?

56
00:03:38,067 --> 00:03:39,900
You're heavy!

57
00:03:39,967 --> 00:03:41,500
I'm not eating anymore.

58
00:03:49,067 --> 00:03:50,200
But I love Tonito.

59
00:03:52,367 --> 00:03:54,033
I love Tonito so much.

60
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:58,300
Tonito brings out
the best in me.

61
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:00,933
He's so good to me.

62
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,067
He's my biggest blessing

63
00:04:02,133 --> 00:04:06,833
and we complement each other.

64
00:04:06,900 --> 00:04:08,267
I can't live without him.

65
00:04:11,700 --> 00:04:13,000
Likewise, Love.

66
00:04:13,067 --> 00:04:15,033
I also can't see myself
being without you.

67
00:04:17,433 --> 00:04:18,500
Tonito...

68
00:04:23,233 --> 00:04:25,133
have you been there that long?

69
00:04:26,300 --> 00:04:28,233
You heard everything I said?

70
00:04:29,133 --> 00:04:30,833
Yes...

71
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:32,067
Why?

72
00:04:32,133 --> 00:04:34,167
Is there anything not true
with what you said about me?

73
00:04:35,167 --> 00:04:37,133
I'm the only Tonito
in your life, isn't it?

74
00:05:07,833 --> 00:05:12,333
Of course, Tonito,
you're my one and only.

75
00:05:27,867 --> 00:05:29,300
Your mom is so beautiful.

76
00:05:30,767 --> 00:05:32,467
I hope that we can visit her
someday.

77
00:05:34,667 --> 00:05:39,100
Well, I think it's time
that I'll introduce her to you.

78
00:05:50,333 --> 00:05:52,533
Mr. Ben, is it still far?

79
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:53,500
We're almost there, Basti!

80
00:05:53,567 --> 00:05:54,733
- We're almost there!
- Hello, Mom?

81
00:05:55,633 --> 00:05:56,800
We're doing an ocular.

82
00:05:56,867 --> 00:06:00,233
So, Mom, this is a remote place
so I might lose signal.

83
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:02,967
Okay. Your Auntie Vivian
just called.

84
00:06:03,033 --> 00:06:05,100
Your dad moved
a very important meeting

85
00:06:05,167 --> 00:06:07,400
to fly to Sorsogon.

86
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:08,867
Did you meet him already?

87
00:06:09,933 --> 00:06:10,900
He's here?

88
00:06:11,933 --> 00:06:13,833
And he didn't
even bother to call me.

89
00:06:15,700 --> 00:06:17,800
I'm sure he chose to be with her
girlfriend than me.

90
00:06:19,267 --> 00:06:21,733
Don't feel bad about your daddy.

91
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:23,200
You know that we both have
the same goal

92
00:06:23,267 --> 00:06:24,700
for your Dad, right?

93
00:06:24,767 --> 00:06:27,833
And that is to make
our family whole again.

94
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:30,333
Your dad is not
the enemy here.

95
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:33,700
The only obstacle to our goal
is none other than Celeste.

96
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:37,667
What you can do is call him
and ask him to see you.

97
00:06:37,733 --> 00:06:40,200
Don't let Celeste have him
all alone to herself.

98
00:06:40,267 --> 00:06:42,300
Hello Mom?

99
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:43,333
Mom?

100
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:45,133
Tiff, did you hear me?

101
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,733
Mom, hello?

102
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:47,800
Mom?

103
00:06:47,867 --> 00:06:49,033
Tiff?

104
00:06:51,700 --> 00:06:52,967
Is that all?

105
00:06:53,033 --> 00:06:54,567
You have nothing else
to tell me?

106
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,767
Grandmother, what else
do you want me to say to you?

107
00:06:57,833 --> 00:06:59,967
I already told you everything.

108
00:07:00,033 --> 00:07:02,167
It's just the two of you
together.

109
00:07:02,233 --> 00:07:03,800
Nothing happened
between the two of you?

110
00:07:05,233 --> 00:07:06,333
You know, Grandmother,
sometimes I would like to think

111
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:07,167
that you also have a dirty mind.

112
00:07:07,233 --> 00:07:08,567
You're saying a lot of...

113
00:07:08,633 --> 00:07:10,033
what are you watching?

114
00:07:10,100 --> 00:07:11,400
You fool.

115
00:07:11,467 --> 00:07:15,400
At my age,
you even think badly of me.

116
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:20,000
What I mean is, didn't you
and Celeste patch things up?

117
00:07:21,500 --> 00:07:24,600
What will I expect
from your love story?

118
00:07:24,667 --> 00:07:27,167
Grandmother, she is now
with the man she will marry.

119
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:30,167
You are embarrassed.

120
00:07:30,233 --> 00:07:31,400
You can't say a word.

121
00:07:32,967 --> 00:07:35,533
You have nothing to expect.

122
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:38,100
Besides, that's nothing to me.

123
00:07:38,167 --> 00:07:40,267
So it's really over
for you and Celeste

124
00:07:40,333 --> 00:07:41,833
even if lightning strikes you?

125
00:07:44,167 --> 00:07:46,467
See?

126
00:07:46,533 --> 00:07:48,933
You can't say it because
lightning might strike you.

127
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:17,900
Hi, Mother.

128
00:08:17,967 --> 00:08:21,167
I'm sad that you're not here
in person

129
00:08:21,267 --> 00:08:25,100
to meet the man I will marry.

130
00:08:26,733 --> 00:08:28,833
But I know you're happy
wherever you are.

131
00:08:30,300 --> 00:08:35,533
But still,
I want to introduce you to...

132
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:38,800
the person whom I really prayed
to come into my life.

133
00:08:40,233 --> 00:08:41,333
This is Tonito.

134
00:08:45,033 --> 00:08:47,167
Hello, Mother.

135
00:08:47,233 --> 00:08:50,533
I hope you will allow me
to call you mother.

136
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:54,367
Celeste and I will get married
in four months.

137
00:08:55,767 --> 00:08:57,567
That's why I'm here to ask
for your consent

138
00:08:57,633 --> 00:08:58,600
to marry your daughter.

139
00:09:00,300 --> 00:09:02,600
And don't worry...

140
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:07,033
I promise
that I will love her forever.

141
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:10,767
I will take care of her

142
00:09:10,833 --> 00:09:13,633
and I will never ever make her
cry.

143
00:09:30,833 --> 00:09:34,700
I know, even if I regret
my mistakes...

144
00:09:35,967 --> 00:09:37,867
I can no longer
bring your life back.

145
00:09:39,067 --> 00:09:43,833
I hope that I can make
our daughter feel the love

146
00:09:43,900 --> 00:09:45,800
that I wasn't able to give you.

147
00:09:46,667 --> 00:09:49,133
I hope that way,
I can make it up

148
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:50,867
for all my shortcomings to you.

149
00:09:57,533 --> 00:09:58,700
Lucinda...

150
00:10:00,033 --> 00:10:02,533
I have long asked
for your forgiveness.

151
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:07,767
I hope that Celeste
can also forgive me.

152
00:10:09,433 --> 00:10:12,200
I have long suffered
from my sin.

153
00:10:14,467 --> 00:10:17,933
I no longer ask that
she'll accept me.

154
00:10:19,567 --> 00:10:22,467
I just hope that...

155
00:10:22,533 --> 00:10:23,967
she can forgive me.

156
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:56,300
Hey, Mr. Ben might see you.

157
00:11:00,233 --> 00:11:01,100
What's your problem?

158
00:11:01,167 --> 00:11:02,767
-Just give me a moment with her.
- Wait.

159
00:11:02,833 --> 00:11:04,100
Dad is calling.

160
00:11:04,167 --> 00:11:05,000
Stay there.

161
00:11:05,067 --> 00:11:06,533
Quiet.

162
00:11:09,100 --> 00:11:10,533
Hello, Dad?

163
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:11,800
Hello, Tiff.

164
00:11:11,867 --> 00:11:13,067
We're on our way to your hotel.

165
00:11:13,133 --> 00:11:14,100
Just wait for us there.

166
00:11:14,933 --> 00:11:17,733
Sorry, Dad,
but we're on a location.

167
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:19,400
Is that so?

168
00:11:19,467 --> 00:11:22,333
I'm with your Auntie Celeste.

169
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:23,567
She wants to see you.

170
00:11:24,667 --> 00:11:25,700
It's okay, Dad.

171
00:11:25,767 --> 00:11:27,067
Just enjoy your day with her.

172
00:11:27,900 --> 00:11:29,533
No. I want to see you.

173
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:30,867
I miss you.

174
00:11:32,067 --> 00:11:33,700
I won't go back to Manila
without seeing you.

175
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:39,100
Don't you want to see me?

176
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:43,000
Tiff...

177
00:11:43,067 --> 00:11:44,200
I'm waiting.

178
00:11:45,500 --> 00:11:47,067
Okay, Dad, but how?

179
00:11:48,067 --> 00:11:49,767
Just text me where you are.

180
00:11:49,833 --> 00:11:52,200
Somehow there's a restaurant
there.

181
00:11:52,267 --> 00:11:53,367
We'll meet you.

182
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:56,000
Okay. I'll just ask around.

183
00:11:57,500 --> 00:11:58,633
See you later, Dad.

184
00:11:58,700 --> 00:12:00,000
All right. You take care.

185
00:12:08,967 --> 00:12:10,967
Celeste?

186
00:12:13,167 --> 00:12:15,033
Sir, Ma'am...

187
00:12:15,133 --> 00:12:17,267
you might want
to join us for snacks?

188
00:12:18,267 --> 00:12:22,967
Tonito, I think it should
just be you and Celeste.

189
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:26,167
Adora and I still have
to attend to some matters.

190
00:12:26,233 --> 00:12:29,267
We will deliver pili
products in Donsol.

191
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:31,733
Are you sure?

192
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:33,700
Yes.

193
00:12:33,767 --> 00:12:35,033
There will be next time.

194
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:39,333
- So, what now?
- Okay.

195
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:42,467
Anyway, thank you
for your invitation.

196
00:12:42,533 --> 00:12:43,467
Welcome, Sir.

197
00:12:44,867 --> 00:12:47,067
Don't call me Sir.

198
00:12:47,133 --> 00:12:49,767
Call me Mr. Patricio

199
00:12:49,867 --> 00:12:54,800
or it would be better
if you just call me father.

200
00:12:54,867 --> 00:12:56,567
Just call me father.

201
00:12:56,633 --> 00:12:58,533
Okay...

202
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,567
father.

203
00:12:59,633 --> 00:13:01,367
Okay.

204
00:13:01,433 --> 00:13:02,633
We should go.

205
00:13:02,700 --> 00:13:07,567
By the way, Celeste, where is
your phone that got wet?

206
00:13:07,633 --> 00:13:09,233
Give it to me. I can fix that.

207
00:13:09,300 --> 00:13:10,433
It will still work.

208
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:11,567
No need, Father.

209
00:13:11,633 --> 00:13:13,267
I can manage.

210
00:13:13,333 --> 00:13:14,667
No, Celeste.

211
00:13:14,733 --> 00:13:17,700
Let's not waste it.
I can fix that.

212
00:13:17,767 --> 00:13:21,233
Let's just let Celeste
have it fixed in the mall.

213
00:13:21,967 --> 00:13:23,900
I can still fix that.

214
00:13:23,967 --> 00:13:25,833
Why let others fix it?

215
00:13:25,900 --> 00:13:27,167
I'll do it.

216
00:13:27,233 --> 00:13:28,600
Celeste...

217
00:13:28,667 --> 00:13:30,567
Okay, Father.

218
00:13:30,633 --> 00:13:31,900
It's in my room.

219
00:13:31,967 --> 00:13:32,933
Just get it.

220
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,367
Okay, Celeste.

221
00:13:34,433 --> 00:13:35,967
I will fix that.
I can still fix that.

222
00:13:36,033 --> 00:13:36,833
What a pity if
we don't fix it.

223
00:13:36,900 --> 00:13:38,267
You can still use that.

224
00:13:38,333 --> 00:13:40,233
Okay, let's go.

225
00:13:40,300 --> 00:13:41,667
Let's leave now.

226
00:13:57,633 --> 00:14:00,900
You will see your dad?

227
00:14:00,967 --> 00:14:02,600
Yes...

228
00:14:02,667 --> 00:14:04,367
even though I don't want to.

229
00:14:04,433 --> 00:14:05,400
Why not?

230
00:14:10,733 --> 00:14:12,567
He is with his fiancé.

231
00:14:12,633 --> 00:14:14,467
Fiance?

232
00:14:14,533 --> 00:14:16,467
You ask a lot of questions.

233
00:14:16,533 --> 00:14:18,433
Just leave her alone, Man.

234
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:19,700
James.

235
00:14:21,033 --> 00:14:23,567
Where will you meet your dad?

236
00:14:24,633 --> 00:14:28,200
There in front of the beach,
by the entrance.

237
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:32,267
Okay, I already texted him.

238
00:14:32,333 --> 00:14:35,667
Boys...

239
00:14:35,733 --> 00:14:40,100
I'll leave
the two of you here.

240
00:14:40,167 --> 00:14:43,233
Can you guys promise me
that you will behave?

241
00:14:47,133 --> 00:14:48,400
I can't hear a promise.

242
00:14:50,367 --> 00:14:51,900
Okay.

243
00:14:51,967 --> 00:14:53,167
Promise?

244
00:14:53,233 --> 00:14:54,433
Promise.

245
00:14:54,867 --> 00:14:57,000
James?

246
00:14:57,067 --> 00:14:59,000
Promise.

247
00:14:59,067 --> 00:15:00,533
Okay.

248
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:04,233
Can you guys
at least, smile at each other?

249
00:15:12,533 --> 00:15:13,933
It looks really good.

250
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:15,433
- Yeah.
- Tender.

251
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:22,267
Hi, Dad.

252
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:23,367
Tiff...

253
00:15:25,733 --> 00:15:26,967
Say hi to your Auntie Celeste.

254
00:15:31,333 --> 00:15:33,533
Tiff, take a seat.

255
00:15:35,533 --> 00:15:37,367
You know,
I ordered a lot already

256
00:15:37,433 --> 00:15:40,033
but if there's anything else
you want, you can order again.

257
00:15:40,100 --> 00:15:41,300
No, thanks.

258
00:16:03,033 --> 00:16:04,367
Dad, I feel bad about you.

259
00:16:06,267 --> 00:16:08,433
Is she more important than me?

260
00:16:10,033 --> 00:16:11,133
Tiff, don't do that.

261
00:16:12,167 --> 00:16:13,467
That's not good!

262
00:16:14,067 --> 00:16:16,233
I really mean for her
not to understand.

263
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:27,033
Honey, how's your project?

264
00:16:28,267 --> 00:16:30,967
Your Auntie Celeste and her
family would love to help you.

265
00:16:31,033 --> 00:16:33,033
I'd rather ask a stranger
for help

266
00:16:33,100 --> 00:16:34,867
rather than ask her
or her family.

267
00:16:36,033 --> 00:16:38,500
Besides, I already found
someone who will help me.

268
00:16:39,733 --> 00:16:40,600
Tiff?

269
00:16:40,667 --> 00:16:42,933
Don't call me Tiff.

270
00:16:44,333 --> 00:16:45,433
We're not close.

271
00:16:50,567 --> 00:16:51,867
Tiffany...

272
00:16:51,933 --> 00:16:53,200
where are your manners?

273
00:16:54,100 --> 00:16:56,833
Why do you talk that way
to your Auntie Celeste?

274
00:16:56,900 --> 00:16:58,967
Dad, what's wrong with that?

275
00:17:00,233 --> 00:17:03,667
Is it wrong to express
what I truly feel?

276
00:17:03,733 --> 00:17:06,500
Tiffany...

277
00:17:06,567 --> 00:17:08,633
I hope you can give me a chance.

278
00:17:08,700 --> 00:17:10,633
You know,
I feel that we can get along.

279
00:17:10,700 --> 00:17:12,400
And why would I do that?

280
00:17:12,467 --> 00:17:14,200
You're the one who ruined
my family

281
00:17:14,267 --> 00:17:16,667
and you want me
to get along with you?

282
00:17:16,767 --> 00:17:17,867
Hell no, Celeste.

283
00:17:17,933 --> 00:17:21,000
Tiffany, your Auntie Celeste
and I didn't come here

284
00:17:21,067 --> 00:17:22,600
for you to disrespect her.

285
00:17:22,667 --> 00:17:24,167
You apologize to her now.

286
00:17:26,367 --> 00:17:27,700
No way.

287
00:17:28,667 --> 00:17:30,333
Tiffany...

288
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:32,200
your Mommy and I
didn't raise you

289
00:17:32,267 --> 00:17:35,033
to be disrespectful
to someone older than you.

290
00:17:35,100 --> 00:17:39,033
And soon, your Auntie Celeste
is going to be my wife.

291
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:40,767
Is that how
you're going to treat her?

292
00:17:46,533 --> 00:17:50,767
I apologize for being rude
and for being honest.

293
00:17:51,700 --> 00:17:53,933
But if you're trying
to attempt to get my sympathy...

294
00:17:56,067 --> 00:17:57,400
I feel so sorry for you...

295
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:01,000
because my loyalty
is with my mom.

296
00:18:05,767 --> 00:18:08,700
Again, I apologize
for being so real.

297
00:18:13,500 --> 00:18:14,567
Dad, I'll just call you.

298
00:18:17,267 --> 00:18:18,900
Tiffany?

299
00:18:18,967 --> 00:18:20,267
Excuse me.

300
00:18:29,767 --> 00:18:31,067
Tiffany!

301
00:18:36,967 --> 00:18:39,400
Dad, I'm sorry.
I'm really not that rude.

302
00:18:42,133 --> 00:18:45,233
I just can't...

303
00:18:45,300 --> 00:18:46,933
Dad, it's hard for me.

304
00:18:49,600 --> 00:18:51,500
How can you and mommy
be okay

305
00:18:51,567 --> 00:18:53,067
if Celeste is in your life?

306
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:56,267
I'm sorry.

307
00:18:56,333 --> 00:18:58,100
I'm really sorry
for disappointing you.

308
00:18:59,167 --> 00:19:01,500
But I just don't want
to give you false hopes

309
00:19:01,567 --> 00:19:03,167
that your mommy and I
will get back together.

310
00:19:04,967 --> 00:19:07,233
We have our own lives now.

311
00:19:07,300 --> 00:19:08,633
How about me?

312
00:19:13,533 --> 00:19:15,800
Didn't you even include me
in the equation?

313
00:19:18,367 --> 00:19:20,267
Am I not your daughter too, Dad?

314
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:25,333
Didn't you even consider me

315
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:28,000
when you decided
to live separately?

316
00:19:32,033 --> 00:19:33,767
I'm really sorry that you got
involved with our problem.

317
00:19:35,067 --> 00:19:38,267
But please, don't hate us.

318
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:43,133
No, Dad, I'm just hurting.

319
00:19:47,100 --> 00:19:49,733
Because every day...

320
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:51,300
every hour, I'm still hoping

321
00:19:51,367 --> 00:19:52,633
that you and mommy will be okay,

322
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:54,733
that we will be complete again.

323
00:19:57,733 --> 00:20:00,833
Honey...

324
00:20:00,900 --> 00:20:03,300
we're still family...

325
00:20:03,400 --> 00:20:06,500
even if your mommy and I
are separated,

326
00:20:06,567 --> 00:20:07,867
I still care for her.

327
00:20:09,467 --> 00:20:12,233
And the most important thing is,
that we both love you.

328
00:20:15,267 --> 00:20:17,967
Even if I'm married
to your Auntie Celeste...

329
00:20:18,033 --> 00:20:19,400
I will still be your dad.

330
00:20:20,333 --> 00:20:22,000
And your Auntie Celeste
can be your mom.

331
00:20:22,067 --> 00:20:23,067
No, Dad.

332
00:20:24,867 --> 00:20:26,667
For me, she's a homewrecker.

333
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:30,300
Why do the two of you
need to get married?

334
00:20:30,367 --> 00:20:32,633
Can it be you and mommy again?

335
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:36,300
Even just for me, Dad?

336
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:40,867
I know that you're mature enough
to understand all of this.

337
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:45,400
And I know...

338
00:20:45,467 --> 00:20:46,967
that one day,
you'd be able to accept this.

339
00:20:48,500 --> 00:20:50,033
Things are hard right now...

340
00:20:51,100 --> 00:20:52,900
but things are going to get
better.

341
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:59,600
Just remember...

342
00:20:59,667 --> 00:21:01,200
I'll always be here for you...

343
00:21:03,067 --> 00:21:04,567
right?

344
00:21:04,633 --> 00:21:06,100
Don't you know that
you're my honey?

345
00:21:06,967 --> 00:21:07,967
My baby monster.

346
00:21:10,933 --> 00:21:12,067
And I will always love you.

347
00:21:13,867 --> 00:21:16,467
So please,
don't feel bad about daddy.

348
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:25,900
I love you so much, Dad.

349
00:21:29,967 --> 00:21:31,667
Please don't ever change.

350
00:21:36,100 --> 00:21:37,233
I won't.

351
00:21:37,300 --> 00:21:38,700
I promise.

352
00:21:38,767 --> 00:21:40,400
And I love you too, very much.

353
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:43,300
And I promise,
I will never change, okay?

354
00:21:49,533 --> 00:21:51,333
But I still don't like
Celeste...

355
00:21:53,133 --> 00:21:54,733
and I feel like I never will.

356
00:21:55,933 --> 00:21:57,333
Well...

357
00:21:57,400 --> 00:22:00,567
all I'm asking is for you
to give her a chance.

358
00:22:01,267 --> 00:22:02,533
I know that you'll get along.

359
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:07,467
I'm sorry, Dad,

360
00:22:07,533 --> 00:22:09,633
but can you just request
something else?

361
00:22:20,067 --> 00:22:21,367
Goodbye, Dad.

362
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:38,867
Hey...

363
00:22:38,933 --> 00:22:41,067
I'm sorry you
and your daughter argued again

364
00:22:41,133 --> 00:22:43,000
because of me.

365
00:22:43,067 --> 00:22:45,700
No need to apologize.

366
00:22:45,767 --> 00:22:47,633
I guess, we just have to give
her some more time

367
00:22:47,700 --> 00:22:49,000
to adjust to the situation.

368
00:22:55,967 --> 00:22:57,633
You know what, Love?

369
00:22:57,700 --> 00:22:59,300
It seems like I don't want
to leave yet.

370
00:23:00,467 --> 00:23:02,967
I want to spend more time here
with you.

371
00:23:05,633 --> 00:23:07,100
You should eat.

372
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:26,933
So, Love,
welcome to Bulusan Lake.

373
00:23:30,967 --> 00:23:32,033
This is amazing, Love.

374
00:23:33,800 --> 00:23:35,500
You're so blessed
that you were born here

375
00:23:35,567 --> 00:23:36,833
and grew up here in Sorsogon.

376
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:40,300
This is paradise.

377
00:23:43,233 --> 00:23:44,367
It is, right?

378
00:23:46,233 --> 00:23:47,700
Well, I've gone through a lot
here,

379
00:23:47,767 --> 00:23:49,100
that's why
I don't want to come back.

380
00:23:51,333 --> 00:23:52,700
Everything happens
for a reason.

381
00:23:54,067 --> 00:23:55,100
I'm just so happy

382
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:58,433
that somehow you and your father
are getting okay.

383
00:24:00,767 --> 00:24:02,400
I don't know.

384
00:24:02,467 --> 00:24:04,367
But it's like my father
and I are not yet okay

385
00:24:04,433 --> 00:24:05,833
and even my stepmom.

386
00:24:07,133 --> 00:24:10,733
I find it hard to forgive them
after everything.

387
00:24:12,067 --> 00:24:16,433
I didn't know that the wounds
of my childhood is deep.

388
00:24:17,800 --> 00:24:19,467
It makes things hard, right?

389
00:24:19,533 --> 00:24:22,933
I wish I don't have baggage
with my family.

390
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:24,233
Who would want that?

391
00:24:25,467 --> 00:24:28,033
But maybe if mother
is still here,

392
00:24:28,100 --> 00:24:30,533
it will be easier for me
to forgive them.

393
00:24:32,667 --> 00:24:33,633
Well...

394
00:24:33,700 --> 00:24:35,500
one forgives to the degree
that one loves.

395
00:24:37,533 --> 00:24:39,133
You are a good person, Celeste.

396
00:24:40,433 --> 00:24:41,667
You are loving.

397
00:24:42,967 --> 00:24:45,000
And I'm confident that sooner
or later,

398
00:24:45,067 --> 00:24:49,000
you will be able
to finally forgive them.

399
00:24:49,067 --> 00:24:51,300
You'll be able
to finally forgive yourself.

400
00:24:56,467 --> 00:24:57,800
Smile, Love.

401
00:25:29,567 --> 00:25:33,400
I'll guess who you will meet.

402
00:25:33,467 --> 00:25:34,467
It's Celeste.

403
00:25:34,533 --> 00:25:36,367
The truth, what happened?

404
00:25:36,467 --> 00:25:37,667
The reason why Mikoy left...

405
00:25:37,733 --> 00:25:39,000
You should tell me.

406
00:25:39,067 --> 00:25:40,000
Do you think this is all real?
What's with you, James?

407
00:25:40,967 --> 00:25:41,867
Are you crazy?
I'm just acting.

408
00:25:42,900 --> 00:25:45,767
Our business
is our top priority, Tonito.

409
00:25:45,833 --> 00:25:48,233
Our family worked hard for it.

410
00:25:48,300 --> 00:25:51,100
We are your family,
not Celeste.

411
00:25:51,167 --> 00:25:53,200
If he didn't scare me
and told me

412
00:25:53,267 --> 00:25:57,000
that there was a big bat there,
I wouldn't be traumatized.

413
00:25:57,067 --> 00:25:59,367
He took advantage
of my vulnerability

414
00:25:59,433 --> 00:26:01,367
with a vested interest.

415
00:26:01,433 --> 00:26:03,967
- Where are we going to sleep?
- Here in my house.

416
00:26:04,033 --> 00:26:06,267
Come on, let's go to sleep.

417
00:26:06,333 --> 00:26:08,167
Where is the shower here?

418
00:26:08,233 --> 00:26:09,200
It's over there!

419
00:26:09,300 --> 00:26:10,433
I took a shower there!

420
00:26:10,500 --> 00:26:11,867
Okay.

421
00:26:20,633 --> 00:26:22,333
What are you doing?
